  "text": "To study the fermentation of dietary carbohydrates in humans, 2 major approaches are used. The first is indirect and collects breath air at regular time intervals to measure the concentration of gases, essentially hydrogen, in volunteers previously given a single oral dose of the carbohydrate [CITATION_1] . The other approach consists of collecting feces after oral feeding and measuring recovery of the tested carbohydrate.",
